Not only did I get a job, but
my childhood dream also came true.

23
00:01:43,040 --> 00:01:44,409
Are you really happy?

24
00:01:44,739 --> 00:01:45,909
I told you, yes.

25
00:01:48,609 --> 00:01:51,879
(Flower of Evil)

26
00:01:52,980 --> 00:01:54,349
I'll give you an hour.

27
00:01:55,519 --> 00:01:57,260
Come to me within an hour.

28
00:02:00,459 --> 00:02:01,530
I miss you.

29
00:02:06,030 --> 00:02:07,069
Yes.

30
00:02:13,340 --> 00:02:15,270
(Episode 10)

31
00:02:25,580 --> 00:02:26,819
I'm Yeom Sang Chul.

32
00:02:29,590 --> 00:02:30,889
You can call me Mr. Yeom.

33
00:02:40,770 --> 00:02:44,270
You're more gullible than I thought.

34
00:02:52,610 --> 00:02:53,750
It's the opposite.

35
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:57,250
It doesn't matter who you are
and what your intentions are.

36
00:02:57,250 --> 00:02:59,080
I don't care why you're taking...

37
00:02:59,419 --> 00:03:00,789
our good.

38
00:03:01,990 --> 00:03:03,189
The thing with our deal...

39
00:03:03,759 --> 00:03:06,719
is that it's more important
that you trust me than I trust you.

40
00:03:07,930 --> 00:03:09,259
What do you mean by that?

41
00:03:47,969 --> 00:03:50,439
(Jaerim-dong)

42
00:03:51,300 --> 00:03:52,469
"Jaerim-dong"?

43
00:03:53,069 --> 00:03:54,969
What is he doing there?

44
00:03:55,069 --> 00:03:57,210
(Husband)

45
00:03:58,680 --> 00:03:59,780
Yes, honey.

46
00:04:00,610 --> 00:04:03,150
Where should I go?
To the police station?

47
00:04:05,780 --> 00:04:07,919
Meet me at the park
in front of the station.

48
00:04:21,870 --> 00:04:23,029
Right.

49
00:04:23,870 --> 00:04:28,139
Put a drop of this on your pillow
before you go to bed.

50
00:04:28,740 --> 00:04:29,810
You'll get a good night's sleep.

51
00:04:33,850 --> 00:04:35,579
I'll leave
after assembling this one.

52
00:04:36,610 --> 00:04:37,879
What are you doing?

53
00:04:38,050 --> 00:04:39,519
I'll be quick.
Just wait a little bit.

54
00:04:40,850 --> 00:04:42,120
That's not what I'm talking about.

55
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:45,459
I'll really be quick.

56
00:04:59,300 --> 00:05:02,009
Hey, this creates a nice mood,

57
00:05:02,339 --> 00:05:03,509
doesn't it?

58
00:05:12,079 --> 00:05:13,920
You ran away
when I needed you the most.

59
00:05:43,550 --> 00:05:45,180
You acted like
you forgot everything,

60
00:05:46,379 --> 00:05:47,550
but you didn't.

61
00:06:05,300 --> 00:06:06,639
(Kim Mu Jin)

62
00:06:30,230 --> 00:06:31,660
I don't want...

63
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,769
to apologize to you
for what happened then.

64
00:06:38,100 --> 00:06:39,500
I never asked for an apology.

65
00:06:41,110 --> 00:06:43,240
I'm telling you
I don't need you anymore.

66
00:06:45,079 --> 00:06:48,009
There isn't a thing
you can do for me.

67
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:53,420
I ran away then.

68
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:57,189
That's why I'm confident...

69
00:06:58,120 --> 00:07:01,829
I'll be able to understand you
better than anyone now.

70
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:08,100
I killed someone.

71
00:07:09,930 --> 00:07:11,269
If that wasn't enough,

72
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:15,110
I made Hyun Su responsible
for what I did.

73
00:07:16,910 --> 00:07:19,139
The person
Hyun Su cherishes the most...

74
00:07:20,579 --> 00:07:22,850
thinks Do Hyun Su
is a brutal murderer.

75
00:07:26,180 --> 00:07:27,750
I need to reveal the truth,

76
00:07:29,990 --> 00:07:31,389
so don't make me get weak.

77
00:07:32,389 --> 00:07:33,420
Hae Su,

78
00:07:34,029 --> 00:07:35,360
that can't be the best way.

79
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:36,759
I said, don't make me get weak!

80
00:07:45,170 --> 00:07:46,199
Hey.

81
00:07:46,939 --> 00:07:50,209
If you shut yourself in your room
and cry alone like that,

82
00:07:50,310 --> 00:07:52,209
that's being really foolish.

83
00:07:52,540 --> 00:07:53,680
You know that?

84
00:08:08,329 --> 00:08:10,430
Why can't I do anything for you?

85
00:08:12,899 --> 00:08:15,300
You might feel sick,

86
00:08:15,970 --> 00:08:18,399
your toilet could get clogged,

87
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:20,839
you might need
to move something heavy,

88
00:08:21,670 --> 00:08:24,709
and you might suddenly get scared
for no reason...

89
00:08:25,379 --> 00:08:26,810
to the point it strangles you.

90
00:08:27,449 --> 00:08:29,750
It doesn't matter...

91
00:08:29,750 --> 00:08:31,550
if it's day or night to me.

92
00:08:33,919 --> 00:08:35,090
If that ever happens, call me.

93
00:08:36,519 --> 00:08:37,659
Okay?

94
00:08:40,159 --> 00:08:41,490
It's not pity.

95
00:08:43,129 --> 00:08:45,230
I don't want us to go back
to the way we were either.

96
00:08:47,769 --> 00:08:48,870
I...

97
00:08:49,830 --> 00:08:52,500
I just don't want you
to endure it alone.

98
00:08:55,139 --> 00:08:56,309
That's all.

99
00:09:16,590 --> 00:09:20,230
(Do Hae Su)

100
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:25,740
This is Cha Ji Won speaking.

101
00:09:26,669 --> 00:09:28,570
I'd like to tell you...

102
00:09:29,570 --> 00:09:30,710
what I couldn't last time.

103
00:09:32,179 --> 00:09:33,279
Sorry?

104
00:09:33,980 --> 00:09:35,049
I know...

105
00:09:37,210 --> 00:09:38,320
who the real killer...

106
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:40,850
of the Gagyeong-ri Village Foreman
Murder Case is.

107
00:09:41,750 --> 00:09:44,120
The real killer?

108
00:09:46,590 --> 00:09:47,730
Hyun Su...

109
00:09:49,929 --> 00:09:51,929
Do Hyun Su is innocent.

110
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:54,000
He didn't kill anyone.

111
00:09:55,529 --> 00:09:56,929
Someone else was the killer.

112
00:10:01,039 --> 00:10:02,210
When it's time...

113
00:10:04,409 --> 00:10:06,210
When I finish what I must do,

114
00:10:08,509 --> 00:10:11,879
I'll tell you everything
about that night.

115
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:15,549
Please remember...

116
00:10:17,490 --> 00:10:18,720
this promise I've made.

117
00:10:56,789 --> 00:10:58,129
It took me exactly 58 minutes.

118
00:11:03,830 --> 00:11:04,970
I was the only one...

119
00:11:05,870 --> 00:11:07,240
you had.

120
00:11:09,470 --> 00:11:10,879
Even now,

121
00:11:12,110 --> 00:11:13,539
I'm the only one you have.

122
00:11:16,179 --> 00:11:17,210
Ji Won.

123
00:11:17,750 --> 00:11:19,320
Are you hurt anywhere?

124
00:11:22,019 --> 00:11:23,250
Why would I be?

125
00:11:27,990 --> 00:11:30,799
- About that call...
- When I said I wanted to break up,

126
00:11:32,500 --> 00:11:33,730
I didn't mean it.

127
00:11:37,029 --> 00:11:38,799
When I said I got sick of you,

128
00:11:40,539 --> 00:11:42,039
that was definitely a lie.

129
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:47,610
Yes. I know.

130
00:11:48,450 --> 00:11:50,509
No, you don't.

131
00:11:55,389 --> 00:11:56,419
I wish...

132
00:11:57,289 --> 00:11:59,720
you could live as me
for just one day.

133
00:12:02,730 --> 00:12:05,259
That way, you'd know how much...

134
00:12:07,570 --> 00:12:09,029
I love you.

135
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:15,570
If that happened,
I wouldn't feel this upset.

136
00:12:20,009 --> 00:12:21,149
Something's...

137
00:12:23,350 --> 00:12:24,450
going on,

138
00:12:25,850 --> 00:12:26,919
right?

139
00:12:43,799 --> 00:12:46,740
Do you even know
what you're saying right now?

140
00:12:47,509 --> 00:12:49,639
You're saying that
a human-trafficking broker...

141
00:12:49,639 --> 00:12:51,340
is involved in a serial murder case!

142
00:12:53,309 --> 00:12:54,679
Can you take responsibility
for what you've said?

143
00:12:55,480 --> 00:12:56,580
Do you have proof?

144
00:12:57,080 --> 00:12:58,549
This is just a speculation, sir.

145
00:12:59,919 --> 00:13:01,389
I need more time.

146
00:13:01,389 --> 00:13:02,590
Time?

147
00:13:03,320 --> 00:13:06,490
What if Hwang Jung Soon dies?
How will you find the mastermind?

148
00:13:10,360 --> 00:13:11,559
The surgery is over.

149
00:13:12,230 --> 00:13:13,429
Tonight will be half the battle.

150
00:13:14,830 --> 00:13:18,539
Gosh, I can't believe
this mess we're in.

151
00:13:19,240 --> 00:13:21,509
We can only continue
our investigation...

152
00:13:21,509 --> 00:13:23,710
once she regains consciousness.

153
00:13:24,639 --> 00:13:27,679
Anyway, let me know
if she's doing any better.

154
00:13:28,250 --> 00:13:29,509
Okay, bye.

155
00:13:36,289 --> 00:13:37,659
(Gangsu Police Station)

156
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:40,889
Detective Choi Jae Seop
of Gangsu Police Station speaking.

157
00:13:43,129 --> 00:13:44,929
Who? Ms. Oh Bok Ja?

158
00:13:45,159 --> 00:13:47,799
I'm Oh Bok Ja
from Homi Village, Gagyeong-ri.

159
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:52,570
Homi Village, Gagyeong-ri,
Namchun-myeon.

160
00:13:52,899 --> 00:13:53,899
Pardon?

161
00:13:54,440 --> 00:13:56,039
Pardon? You have a picture
of Do Hyun Su...

162
00:13:56,039 --> 00:13:57,210
from five years ago?

163
00:13:57,879 --> 00:14:00,809
- Don't you remember me?
- Of course, I do, ma'am.

164
00:14:00,809 --> 00:14:03,450
Hello, ma'am. What is it?

165
00:14:03,879 --> 00:14:07,889
I had returned home today
after staying with my daughter.

166
00:14:08,620 --> 00:14:11,360
I was cleaning the house...

167
00:14:11,360 --> 00:14:13,759
and found a strange-looking object.

168
00:14:20,429 --> 00:14:21,500
What is this?

169
00:14:24,029 --> 00:14:26,139
(Gangsu Police Station)

170
00:14:26,139 --> 00:14:28,139
Why didn't I think
that Hwang Jung Soon...

171
00:14:28,139 --> 00:14:31,210
could've climbed out of the window
while I was away?

172
00:14:33,039 --> 00:14:34,210
I was too conceited.

173
00:14:34,210 --> 00:14:35,250
(Gangsu Police Station)

174
00:14:35,250 --> 00:14:36,779
I feel too ashamed
to see my teammates.

175
00:14:37,950 --> 00:14:39,320
Is the situation that bad right now?

176
00:14:44,490 --> 00:14:46,419
I'm too exhausted
to continue working.

177
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:49,029
You should be
the breadwinner instead.

178
00:14:54,029 --> 00:14:55,100
I mean...

179
00:14:56,529 --> 00:14:59,039
In two years,
Eun Ha will be attending school.

180
00:15:00,100 --> 00:15:01,940
I had been thinking about this
for a while now.

181
00:15:03,110 --> 00:15:04,379
How about sending her
to a school in the countryside?

182
00:15:05,009 --> 00:15:06,139
That's the trend nowadays.

183
00:15:08,549 --> 00:15:10,409
Once this case is over,

184
00:15:13,919 --> 00:15:15,789
I want to raise Eun Ha
and live quietly...

185
00:15:15,789 --> 00:15:17,220
where there's fresh air.

186
00:15:19,159 --> 00:15:20,259
Would you...

187
00:15:21,659 --> 00:15:22,830
like that?

188
00:15:32,440 --> 00:15:33,570
(Cha Ji Won, National Police Agency)

189
00:15:33,570 --> 00:15:35,740
I can still vividly remember
the time...

190
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:39,779
when you were so elated
to have this around your neck.

191
00:15:41,379 --> 00:15:42,450
(Cha Ji Won, National Police Agency)

192
00:15:42,450 --> 00:15:43,509
That's okay.

193
00:15:44,419 --> 00:15:45,549
It's become a boring job now.

194
00:15:47,419 --> 00:15:50,889
You seem a bit off today.

195
00:15:52,460 --> 00:15:53,559
Don't be ridiculous.

196
00:15:54,889 --> 00:15:57,090
Go home, now. I should go in.

197
00:15:57,899 --> 00:15:59,200
I have loads of work.

198
00:16:00,100 --> 00:16:01,200
Bye.

199
00:16:56,389 --> 00:16:57,419
I'm sorry,

200
00:16:58,759 --> 00:17:00,019
but I have to go.

201
00:17:20,109 --> 00:17:22,880
Wait for my call
at midnight tonight.

202
00:17:38,900 --> 00:17:39,930
Talk.

203
00:17:39,930 --> 00:17:41,700
We'll make our deal tomorrow
at midnight.

204
00:17:42,829 --> 00:17:45,039
But first, bring 100,000 dollars
to my office.

205
00:18:04,660 --> 00:18:07,019
If you pick one of them,
I can bring them to you by tomorrow.

206
00:18:07,589 --> 00:18:10,089
If you want to make an order,
it'll take some time.

207
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:15,500
Do none of them interest you?

208
00:18:17,529 --> 00:18:18,599
That kid.

209
00:18:19,839 --> 00:18:21,039
I'll take the kid.

210
00:18:50,769 --> 00:18:53,240
Do Min Seok's accomplice's name
and photo.

211
00:18:55,670 --> 00:18:56,769
I want them too.

212
00:19:11,220 --> 00:19:12,289
You're making it...

213
00:19:14,990 --> 00:19:16,160
difficult to refuse.

214
00:19:19,160 --> 00:19:20,829
Get our new customer a phone.

215
00:19:28,369 --> 00:19:29,509
It's a burner phone.

216
00:19:30,640 --> 00:19:32,039
We'll only keep in touch using this.

217
00:19:33,740 --> 00:19:36,150
I'll explain the rules
of our deal, so listen carefully.

218
00:19:36,150 --> 00:19:39,349
If you disobey the rules,
our deal is off immediately.

219
00:19:39,480 --> 00:19:42,220
If our deal is called off,
I will not hesitate for a second...

220
00:19:42,690 --> 00:19:44,819
to get rid of all the evidence.

221
00:19:46,019 --> 00:19:47,559
And what I mean by evidence,

222
00:19:49,430 --> 00:19:50,859
it includes people as well.

223
00:20:12,619 --> 00:20:14,549
So...

224
00:20:16,990 --> 00:20:20,519
The person who I hit...

225
00:20:21,589 --> 00:20:23,859
with my car...

226
00:20:25,460 --> 00:20:27,130
is living...

227
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:30,430
as me right now?

228
00:20:34,170 --> 00:20:37,109
We determined that it was
hard for you to survive.

229
00:20:39,309 --> 00:20:41,579
Then... Then...

230
00:20:43,750 --> 00:20:44,849
What about me?

231
00:20:46,720 --> 00:20:49,990
How do I live...

232
00:20:50,319 --> 00:20:51,359
from now on?

233
00:20:56,059 --> 00:20:57,730
What will happen...

234
00:20:58,730 --> 00:21:02,269
to my life?

235
00:21:04,869 --> 00:21:07,140
Just tell me that.

236
00:21:09,569 --> 00:21:11,480
I'll live the way...

237
00:21:13,079 --> 00:21:15,309
you and Mom want me...

238
00:21:17,150 --> 00:21:18,319
to live.

239
00:21:26,059 --> 00:21:27,220
Dad.

240
00:21:30,589 --> 00:21:32,400
Can't you...

241
00:21:33,029 --> 00:21:34,799
ask him?

242
00:21:36,470 --> 00:21:39,099
To give me back my name?

243
00:21:42,240 --> 00:21:43,740
I will...

244
00:21:44,880 --> 00:21:48,279
I will meet him and ask him.

245
00:21:49,309 --> 00:21:52,349
Let me meet him.

246
00:21:58,059 --> 00:22:01,660
(Hee Seong)

247
00:22:09,069 --> 00:22:10,970
Why are you calling so late?

248
00:22:11,900 --> 00:22:13,400
I have a favor to ask you.

249
00:22:14,640 --> 00:22:15,769
A favor?

250
00:22:16,009 --> 00:22:19,240
I need money.
100,000 dollars in cash.

251
00:22:19,779 --> 00:22:20,940
What do you need it for?

252
00:22:23,009 --> 00:22:26,250
I think I can find the accomplice
of the Yeonju Serial Murder Case.

253
00:22:34,220 --> 00:22:35,289
How?

254
00:22:36,059 --> 00:22:38,359
I found someone who knows about
the accomplice.

255
00:22:39,430 --> 00:22:40,900
They want money in trade
for the information.

256
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:43,230
You don't want...

257
00:22:44,130 --> 00:22:47,440
Do Hyun Su's name being mentioned
anymore either.

258
00:22:49,869 --> 00:22:50,970
I'll see you tomorrow.

259
00:22:51,809 --> 00:22:53,039
Come to the hospital.

260
00:22:59,150 --> 00:23:00,980
What is it? What did Hee Seong...

261
00:23:02,450 --> 00:23:04,390
What did Hyun Su say?

262
00:23:06,789 --> 00:23:08,059
It's nothing.

263
00:23:15,930 --> 00:23:17,299
Dad.

264
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:22,539
Let me meet him.

265
00:23:25,309 --> 00:23:26,539
Never.

266
00:23:26,809 --> 00:23:28,480
Why not?

267
00:23:31,009 --> 00:23:33,680
If he sees me in person,

268
00:23:34,789 --> 00:23:37,589
he might feel pity.

269
00:23:41,460 --> 00:23:43,390
He's not someone
you can underestimate.

270
00:23:45,500 --> 00:23:47,660
If he finds out you're awake,

271
00:23:48,930 --> 00:23:51,000
your presence will bother him.

272
00:23:59,609 --> 00:24:00,910
Then...

273
00:24:01,710 --> 00:24:04,309
what will you do?

274
00:24:05,779 --> 00:24:07,619
What can I do?

275
00:24:09,789 --> 00:24:11,019
I'll just...

276
00:24:12,089 --> 00:24:15,460
have to hope we get lucky.

277
00:25:20,359 --> 00:25:23,190
Let's learn about happy expressions.

278
00:25:23,890 --> 00:25:26,000
Number one, wrinkles develop
around your eyes.

279
00:25:26,500 --> 00:25:29,569
Number two, your cheeks go up.

280
00:25:30,000 --> 00:25:33,940
Number three, you can feel
the wrinkles around your eyes...

281
00:25:33,940 --> 00:25:35,369
move slightly.

282
00:26:23,819 --> 00:26:25,890
Are you leaving already?
You didn't get enough sleep.

283
00:26:26,759 --> 00:26:29,559
Something urgent came up.
Hwang Jung Soon died.

284
00:26:29,559 --> 00:26:31,289
What? Ji Won.

285
00:26:32,430 --> 00:26:33,500
Wait.

286
00:26:38,869 --> 00:26:39,940
Why aren't you asking me?

287
00:26:41,599 --> 00:26:42,670
Ask you what?

288
00:26:43,140 --> 00:26:45,140
What I did last night with whom.

289
00:26:45,579 --> 00:26:47,480
And why I answered
the phone like that.

290
00:26:49,309 --> 00:26:51,549
Tell me when you really want to.

291
00:26:53,450 --> 00:26:55,049
I'm ready to listen anytime.

292
00:27:02,930 --> 00:27:04,089
See you later.

293
00:27:04,759 --> 00:27:07,559
Everything will go well.
Don't worry too much.

294
00:27:38,460 --> 00:27:40,730
I'm Chief Yoon Sang Pil
of the violent crimes unit.

295
00:27:41,029 --> 00:27:42,269
I'll head today's briefing...

296
00:27:42,269 --> 00:27:44,700
for the reinvestigation of the
Yeonju Serial Murder Case.

297
00:27:45,640 --> 00:27:47,470
We've already provided you
with the press release.

298
00:27:48,099 --> 00:27:50,140
We'll receive any questions
you may have now.

299
00:27:52,240 --> 00:27:53,240
Yes?

300
00:27:53,539 --> 00:27:55,180
I'm Park Jin Gyu of K-news.

301
00:27:55,880 --> 00:27:58,210
It's difficult to determine how
Hwang Jung Soon is related...

302
00:27:58,210 --> 00:28:00,920
to the serial murder case
based on this press release only.

303
00:28:01,680 --> 00:28:04,549
Also, we want to hear your position
on whether your sting operation...

304
00:28:04,720 --> 00:28:06,390
was legitimate when it led to
someone's death.

305
00:28:16,529 --> 00:28:18,329
Did you check Hwang Jung Soon's
bank account?

306
00:28:19,740 --> 00:28:21,869
There's nothing special.
What stands out...

307
00:28:21,940 --> 00:28:25,109
is that she wired money once a month
regularly to a sanatorium.

308
00:28:25,509 --> 00:28:27,309
Her mother has Alzheimer's.

309
00:28:30,109 --> 00:28:31,819
Did you find out
where she went yesterday?

310
00:28:33,519 --> 00:28:37,150
She went to a market in Jaerim-dong,
and that's as far as I know.

311
00:28:37,990 --> 00:28:39,059
Jaerim-dong?

312
00:28:39,420 --> 00:28:40,660
Yes. Why?

313
00:28:41,930 --> 00:28:42,960
It's nothing.

314
00:28:45,329 --> 00:28:47,200
There's no one coming
to collect her body,

315
00:28:47,200 --> 00:28:48,670
let alone hold a funeral.

316
00:28:55,369 --> 00:28:57,670
By the way, didn't you go
to Gagyeong-ri yesterday?

317
00:28:58,640 --> 00:29:01,240
That? It was nothing much.

318
00:29:01,950 --> 00:29:03,109
Why did you go there?

319
00:29:04,349 --> 00:29:05,750
Well, just...

320
00:29:16,690 --> 00:29:17,730
Yes?

321
00:29:17,829 --> 00:29:20,430
I'm Detective Cha Ji Won
from Gangsu Police Station.

322
00:29:24,299 --> 00:29:25,299
Hello?

323
00:29:27,140 --> 00:29:28,269
Please go ahead.

324
00:29:29,210 --> 00:29:32,710
I have something important to report
about the Yeonju Serial Murder Case.

325
00:29:35,750 --> 00:29:37,450
May I ask who's calling?

326
00:29:39,650 --> 00:29:40,750
I'm Do Hyun Su.

327
00:29:48,119 --> 00:29:49,829
May I ask who's calling?

328
00:29:52,029 --> 00:29:53,130
I'm Do Hyun Su.

329
00:29:59,839 --> 00:30:00,869
Who?

330
00:30:12,250 --> 00:30:13,420
I'm Do Hyun Su.

331
00:30:21,660 --> 00:30:23,890
What is it, Ji Won?

332
00:30:25,500 --> 00:30:26,559
Hello?

333
00:30:32,369 --> 00:30:33,500
Please go ahead.

334
00:30:36,240 --> 00:30:37,339
Who?

335
00:30:38,609 --> 00:30:41,210
"Do Hyun Su"? The Do Hyun Su?

336
00:30:41,740 --> 00:30:43,450
Do Min Seok's son Do Hyun Su?

337
00:30:47,119 --> 00:30:49,319
How many times are you making me
introduce myself?

338
00:30:49,750 --> 00:30:53,619
You punk. You'll get in trouble
if you prank call the police.

339
00:30:55,390 --> 00:30:57,630
I'm going to help you
catch the accomplice,

340
00:30:57,890 --> 00:30:59,160
but you're being too rude.

341
00:30:59,700 --> 00:31:01,059
Now I want to hang up.

342
00:31:01,859 --> 00:31:04,470
Wait. Please hold on.

343
00:31:06,470 --> 00:31:07,539
He says he's Do Hyun Su.

344
00:31:08,640 --> 00:31:10,210
He identified himself as Do Hyun Su.

345
00:31:16,279 --> 00:31:20,319
Rule one. Do not carry any wireless
devices right after the deal.

346
00:31:20,549 --> 00:31:21,650
Rule two.

347
00:31:22,650 --> 00:31:24,019
I'll check the money first.

348
00:31:24,089 --> 00:31:26,460
Rule three.
Once I've checked the money,

349
00:31:26,859 --> 00:31:29,289
you're to move to
a designated place to get your good.

350
00:31:29,289 --> 00:31:30,430
Simple, right?

351
00:31:31,960 --> 00:31:33,529
The picture of the man you want...

352
00:31:34,230 --> 00:31:36,400
will be handed to you on the spot
after I check my money.

353
00:31:46,279 --> 00:31:47,440
Mr. Do Hyun Su.

354
00:31:48,240 --> 00:31:51,509
We'll put you on speakerphone
from now on. Is that okay?

355
00:31:54,019 --> 00:31:55,049
Okay.

356
00:31:57,019 --> 00:32:00,390
How many detectives
am I speaking to right now?

357
00:32:01,319 --> 00:32:02,460
Four.

358
00:32:03,359 --> 00:32:06,759
No one else should know about
this phone call.

359
00:32:08,059 --> 00:32:09,569
Can you promise me?

360
00:32:20,440 --> 00:32:21,640
I promise.

361
00:32:24,279 --> 00:32:27,450
I'd like to inform you
that I'm also recording this call.

362
00:32:28,450 --> 00:32:30,890
What information do you have?

363
00:32:34,190 --> 00:32:38,089
There's a human trafficking
organization that abducted...

364
00:32:38,089 --> 00:32:39,559
and sold people to Do Min Seok
and his accomplice.

365
00:32:41,029 --> 00:32:43,069
I know about the organization.

366
00:32:52,109 --> 00:32:54,710
Do Min Seok and the accomplice
were supplied...

367
00:32:55,349 --> 00:32:57,049
with the victims
through that organization.

368
00:33:00,450 --> 00:33:03,950
Tonight, I'll be making
a deal with that organization.

369
00:33:07,359 --> 00:33:08,789
I'll be getting a victim
who was confined,

370
00:33:09,559 --> 00:33:12,130
as well as some information
about the accomplice.

371
00:33:14,730 --> 00:33:18,740
I can create the golden opportunity
for you to raid the scene.

372
00:33:20,440 --> 00:33:22,509
What time is it happening? Where?

373
00:33:25,910 --> 00:33:27,039
Now...

374
00:33:28,339 --> 00:33:30,079
I'll tell you my conditions.

375
00:33:31,180 --> 00:33:32,549
As you might have guessed,

376
00:33:33,180 --> 00:33:35,119
this phone was registered
under someone else.

377
00:33:36,049 --> 00:33:37,089
Also,

378
00:33:39,990 --> 00:33:42,390
even if you track my location now,

379
00:33:44,529 --> 00:33:46,430
it won't be easy to find me.

380
00:33:47,759 --> 00:33:50,670
I'll share all the information
I know...

381
00:33:51,200 --> 00:33:53,670
so you can close
the Yeonju Serial Murder Case.

382
00:33:56,140 --> 00:33:59,880
I want you to swear on your honor
and promise...

383
00:34:00,109 --> 00:34:02,210
to keep my identity a secret.

384
00:34:02,880 --> 00:34:06,349
Also, all the information
you collect from this call...

385
00:34:07,019 --> 00:34:09,389
must be discarded
when the investigation closes.

386
00:34:12,889 --> 00:34:14,289
Anything else?

387
00:34:16,489 --> 00:34:18,190
- That's all.
- Wait.

388
00:34:18,829 --> 00:34:20,000
That's all?

389
00:34:20,630 --> 00:34:23,030
You've been on the run
for almost 20 years.

390
00:34:23,030 --> 00:34:26,039
Did you call the police
just for the sake of justice?

391
00:34:26,039 --> 00:34:27,769
Do you expect us to believe that?

392
00:34:31,210 --> 00:34:33,239
I'm not Do Min Seok's accomplice.

393
00:34:34,980 --> 00:34:36,510
I want to prove that.

394
00:34:38,710 --> 00:34:41,519
I guess he really isn't
the accomplice.

395
00:34:41,820 --> 00:34:43,349
How can we trust that?

396
00:34:44,849 --> 00:34:48,789
I'm not even sure
if you're really Do Hyun Su...

397
00:34:48,889 --> 00:34:51,389
or if you're a lunatic.

398
00:34:51,389 --> 00:34:52,630
Mr. Do Hyun Su.

399
00:34:57,070 --> 00:34:58,199
Yes?

400
00:34:59,070 --> 00:35:00,199
Let's do it this way.

401
00:35:02,639 --> 00:35:06,340
Tell us about the person
who sold people to Do Min Seok.

402
00:35:07,409 --> 00:35:09,480
After we verify the information,

403
00:35:10,409 --> 00:35:13,280
we'll determine if your report
is reliable or not.

404
00:35:14,019 --> 00:35:15,849
Then, we'll ask
for the next information.

405
00:35:16,789 --> 00:35:20,719
If we end up getting
additional information from you,

406
00:35:20,719 --> 00:35:22,059
we'll meet your demands.

407
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:32,099
All right.

408
00:35:33,440 --> 00:35:35,539
I'll give you some information
about Yeom Sang Chul.

409
00:35:36,639 --> 00:35:37,840
"Yeom Sang Chul"?

410
00:35:38,769 --> 00:35:40,409
Please act with caution.

411
00:35:41,440 --> 00:35:43,010
If he catches on,

412
00:35:45,349 --> 00:35:47,380
all the confined victims will die.

413
00:35:48,449 --> 00:35:49,449
And...

414
00:35:52,050 --> 00:35:53,260
I'll be gone as well.

415
00:36:18,710 --> 00:36:19,719
Yes, Ji Won.

416
00:36:23,690 --> 00:36:24,690
What are you doing?

417
00:36:25,320 --> 00:36:27,320
I'm out to get supplies. What is it?

418
00:36:28,159 --> 00:36:29,230
Honey.

419
00:36:30,230 --> 00:36:31,889
Can you pick me up later?

420
00:36:32,699 --> 00:36:34,199
Let's have dinner together.

421
00:36:35,800 --> 00:36:39,199
Let's go to that spicy noodle place
we went to last time.

422
00:36:39,199 --> 00:36:40,539
I'm craving it.

423
00:36:44,769 --> 00:36:48,309
Right.
I don't think I can go home tonight.

424
00:36:51,179 --> 00:36:52,349
Why not?

425
00:36:52,349 --> 00:36:53,880
I have to go to a funeral.

426
00:36:54,880 --> 00:36:56,489
The father of a client passed away.

427
00:36:57,050 --> 00:36:58,090
Don't go.

428
00:37:01,389 --> 00:37:02,530
Why not?

429
00:37:03,090 --> 00:37:05,230
Don't go. I don't want you to go.

430
00:37:08,500 --> 00:37:09,670
Ji Won.

431
00:37:16,610 --> 00:37:17,769
Actually,

432
00:37:20,909 --> 00:37:23,179
I had a really bad dream last night.

433
00:37:27,619 --> 00:37:31,219
See? It's because you didn't get
any proper sleep.

434
00:37:32,250 --> 00:37:35,090
Are you going to go?

435
00:37:35,889 --> 00:37:38,030
Yes. I have to.

436
00:37:39,800 --> 00:37:41,000
Do whatever you want.

437
00:37:41,960 --> 00:37:43,630
- I'm hanging up.
- Ji Won.

438
00:37:46,099 --> 00:37:47,199
I...

439
00:37:48,469 --> 00:37:50,110
want to become someone
that's good enough...

440
00:37:52,440 --> 00:37:53,610
for you.

441
00:37:54,909 --> 00:37:56,349
Someone good enough.

442
00:38:06,320 --> 00:38:07,820
I have to go back to work.

443
00:38:09,190 --> 00:38:10,429
I'll call you...

444
00:38:13,760 --> 00:38:15,500
around 10pm later.

445
00:38:16,630 --> 00:38:18,099
Okay. Sure.

446
00:38:56,710 --> 00:38:57,739
Aren't you cold?

447
00:38:58,739 --> 00:39:00,440
It's okay.

448
00:39:02,210 --> 00:39:03,710
I can be outside.

449
00:39:25,469 --> 00:39:27,699
Would you like a cup of warm tea?

450
00:39:29,110 --> 00:39:30,510
Thank you.

451
00:39:38,349 --> 00:39:39,619
How much...

452
00:39:40,750 --> 00:39:42,380
does she know?

453
00:39:48,090 --> 00:39:51,289
We purposely hired someone
who couldn't read lips.

454
00:39:52,159 --> 00:39:53,960
She also signed
a confidential agreement.

455
00:39:55,969 --> 00:39:59,170
Even if she knew something,
she wouldn't tell it to anyone.

456
00:40:05,510 --> 00:40:06,539
Hee Seong.

457
00:40:08,480 --> 00:40:10,050
Who was the person...

458
00:40:12,679 --> 00:40:14,920
you said you had...

459
00:40:15,820 --> 00:40:16,849
to meet?

460
00:40:22,559 --> 00:40:23,630
A woman.

461
00:40:24,590 --> 00:40:25,690
A woman?

462
00:40:27,059 --> 00:40:29,699
Had there not been an accident
that day,

463
00:40:31,670 --> 00:40:33,969
we would've met.

464
00:40:36,070 --> 00:40:37,469
And if we had met,

465
00:40:40,309 --> 00:40:42,239
our fates...

466
00:40:45,050 --> 00:40:47,349
would've changed completely.

467
00:40:55,460 --> 00:40:57,829
(The Three Mysteries about
Jung Mi Sook's Disappearance)

468
00:41:02,159 --> 00:41:04,670
"The Three Mysteries about
Jung Mi Sook's Disappearance."

469
00:41:08,239 --> 00:41:11,139
Everyone knows this information.
It's just the title that's enticing.

470
00:41:11,409 --> 00:41:14,139
That's exactly the point.
It's enticing.

471
00:41:20,079 --> 00:41:22,619
- What?
- You're quite the wily type.

472
00:41:23,289 --> 00:41:24,750
Don't beat around the bush
and just give it to me.

473
00:41:24,949 --> 00:41:27,559
- Give what?
- Do Hae Su's exclusive interview.

474
00:41:28,420 --> 00:41:29,690
There's no such thing.

475
00:41:29,690 --> 00:41:32,360
She came here saying
she'd only talk with you.

476
00:41:32,760 --> 00:41:34,400
If you didn't interview her,
then what did you do?

477
00:41:35,659 --> 00:41:36,699
Confess my feelings?

478
00:41:37,630 --> 00:41:39,739
Are you saying
you two are going out?

479
00:41:40,940 --> 00:41:41,969
No.

480
00:41:42,400 --> 00:41:43,539
Did she reject you?

481
00:41:43,809 --> 00:41:44,840
Yes.

482
00:41:45,110 --> 00:41:46,280
That's great.

483
00:41:46,539 --> 00:41:48,380
Just interview her.
What's stopping you?

484
00:41:48,980 --> 00:41:51,449
How can you be so inhumane?

485
00:41:55,650 --> 00:41:57,619
Let's meet. It's important.

486
00:41:59,460 --> 00:42:00,619
I'm going to do some legwork.

487
00:42:00,659 --> 00:42:02,059
Mu Jin.

488
00:42:04,489 --> 00:42:06,130
I fell in love
while interviewing someone...

489
00:42:06,130 --> 00:42:07,400
and even got married to him.

490
00:42:08,199 --> 00:42:09,369
But you divorced him.

491
00:42:10,329 --> 00:42:13,139
You said you were too rash
and told me to be careful.

492
00:42:13,599 --> 00:42:15,369
That's a different issue.

493
00:42:15,369 --> 00:42:17,610
- Get lost right now!
- Yes, ma'am.

494
00:42:19,440 --> 00:42:22,579
Ms. Do, you're the wind.

495
00:42:23,949 --> 00:42:25,809
You can go wherever you want.

496
00:42:27,280 --> 00:42:28,880
When I count to three,

497
00:42:29,150 --> 00:42:32,690
you'll arrive
at your father's funeral.

498
00:42:33,960 --> 00:42:35,059
One,

499
00:42:36,260 --> 00:42:37,329
two,

500
00:42:38,289 --> 00:42:39,300
three.

501
00:42:49,369 --> 00:42:50,409
Ms. Do?

502
00:42:51,340 --> 00:42:52,980
You have more than enough time.

503
00:42:53,809 --> 00:42:56,610
Take your time
to observe the culprit.

504
00:43:05,619 --> 00:43:06,789
Something's strange.

505
00:43:08,719 --> 00:43:10,559
His left fingernails...

506
00:43:12,630 --> 00:43:14,000
are too short.

507
00:43:16,570 --> 00:43:18,469
It must be uncomfortable for him.

508
00:43:18,969 --> 00:43:20,170
You're doing well.

509
00:43:24,369 --> 00:43:26,239
What? I think I've seen...

510
00:43:27,280 --> 00:43:28,710
that design before.

511
00:43:30,510 --> 00:43:31,980
Where did I see it?

512
00:43:34,519 --> 00:43:36,789
How does the culprit look?

513
00:43:44,929 --> 00:43:46,030
He is...

514
00:43:46,829 --> 00:43:49,469
looking at me slowly.

515
00:43:51,329 --> 00:43:52,500
He's studying...

516
00:43:53,639 --> 00:43:55,570
every inch of my face.

517
00:43:58,739 --> 00:44:00,610
He's trying to remember my face.

518
00:44:03,309 --> 00:44:04,349
I'm scared.

519
00:44:05,349 --> 00:44:06,679
Get me out of here.

520
00:44:06,920 --> 00:44:09,420
Ms. Do, open your eyes
on the count of three.

521
00:44:09,420 --> 00:44:11,250
1, 2, 3.

522
00:44:16,030 --> 00:44:17,760
He was trying to remember my face.

523
00:44:19,599 --> 00:44:21,000
Don't you know what that means?

524
00:44:25,300 --> 00:44:26,300
He's going...

525
00:44:27,300 --> 00:44:28,639
to kill me.

526
00:44:29,440 --> 00:44:32,010
Ms. Do, calm down.

527
00:44:32,239 --> 00:44:34,340
What you just experienced...

528
00:44:34,340 --> 00:44:35,909
happened 18 years ago.

529
00:44:37,050 --> 00:44:38,880
You're fine. Nothing will happen.

530
00:44:39,949 --> 00:44:41,250
Trust me.

531
00:44:43,119 --> 00:44:45,389
I don't think you should drive
back home.

532
00:44:46,090 --> 00:44:48,360
Do you have anyone to call?

533
00:44:48,360 --> 00:44:49,360
I'm fine.

534
00:44:50,429 --> 00:44:51,530
I need a break.

535
00:44:56,929 --> 00:45:00,500
(Mu Jin)

