00:45:01,699 --> 00:45:03,840
Yeom Sang Chul, born in 1973.

538
00:45:04,340 --> 00:45:05,739
In 1990 at the age of 17,

539
00:45:05,739 --> 00:45:07,340
he was sentenced
to ten years of prison...

540
00:45:07,340 --> 00:45:08,710
for attempted murder and arson.

541
00:45:08,909 --> 00:45:10,380
However, he was released on parole
in 1997...

542
00:45:10,380 --> 00:45:12,050
on the condition of doing
community service.

543
00:45:12,179 --> 00:45:15,219
What's important is that
after he was released,

544
00:45:15,219 --> 00:45:16,650
he did community service...

545
00:45:18,150 --> 00:45:20,659
at Deep Spring
Child Guidance Clinic.

546
00:45:21,789 --> 00:45:23,530
Is that...

547
00:45:23,530 --> 00:45:27,130
That's where Do Hyun Su
was treated from 1997 to 1999.

548
00:45:27,800 --> 00:45:30,769
That means Yeom Sang Chul
and Do Min Seok could've met.

549
00:45:31,469 --> 00:45:32,530
Exactly.

550
00:45:32,800 --> 00:45:35,139
What about him and Hwang Jung Soon?

551
00:45:35,300 --> 00:45:38,909
Yeom is running an employment agency
in Jaerim-dong.

552
00:45:39,340 --> 00:45:40,380
Ho Joon.

553
00:45:41,909 --> 00:45:43,280
This was yesterday.

554
00:45:43,750 --> 00:45:46,619
The CCTV camera in the parking lot
across his employment agency...

555
00:45:46,619 --> 00:45:47,880
caught her.

556
00:45:49,019 --> 00:45:52,789
This means Do Hyun Su's tip-off
is credible.

557
00:45:53,260 --> 00:45:55,590
Yes, I'm sure of it.

558
00:45:56,789 --> 00:45:58,230
How could
a human-trafficking gang...

559
00:45:58,230 --> 00:46:00,730
get involved
in a serial murder case?

560
00:46:01,329 --> 00:46:03,530
This is unbelievable.

561
00:46:03,670 --> 00:46:06,469
If we catch all of them,

562
00:46:07,440 --> 00:46:09,739
every single one of us
will receive a special promotion.

563
00:46:10,639 --> 00:46:12,710
Don't get ahead of yourself.

564
00:46:12,710 --> 00:46:16,349
We're catching Do Hyun Su too,
right?

565
00:46:25,650 --> 00:46:26,659
Are you okay?

566
00:46:27,989 --> 00:46:29,860
Let me come with you from now on.

567
00:46:31,760 --> 00:46:34,260
You're not supposed to drive
after receiving hypnotherapy.

568
00:46:34,760 --> 00:46:36,130
I'm going to find another therapist.

569
00:46:36,730 --> 00:46:38,630
I can't trust someone who answered
my phone without my consent.

570
00:46:40,500 --> 00:46:41,769
She only picked up...

571
00:46:42,139 --> 00:46:44,840
because the name you saved me as
sounded very friendly.

572
00:46:48,110 --> 00:46:49,809
(Mu Jin)

573
00:46:50,909 --> 00:46:52,510
(Reporter Kim)

574
00:46:57,519 --> 00:46:58,849
Open up your heart, will you?

575
00:46:59,190 --> 00:47:01,019
Why should I open my heart to you?

576
00:47:02,059 --> 00:47:03,889
Not to me but your therapist.

577
00:47:07,860 --> 00:47:10,570
She said your suspicions
and anxiety toward others...

578
00:47:10,570 --> 00:47:11,869
are deeply rooted.

579
00:47:12,570 --> 00:47:16,039
Because of that, she said
you may be creating your own fears.

580
00:47:21,110 --> 00:47:22,409
Why did Hyun Su contact you?

581
00:47:23,949 --> 00:47:25,050
I'm not sure.

582
00:47:25,309 --> 00:47:27,980
Yesterday, he said
he remembered something and left.

583
00:47:28,219 --> 00:47:29,750
Perhaps, it's about that.

584
00:47:32,719 --> 00:47:34,460
You're going to deceive Do Hyun Su?

585
00:47:35,059 --> 00:47:37,690
Didn't we promise to keep him safe
in exchange for the information?

586
00:47:37,829 --> 00:47:40,929
What kind of detective
protects murderers?

587
00:47:41,059 --> 00:47:43,670
There's no such law. Aren't I right?

588
00:47:45,030 --> 00:47:46,800
You're right about that.

589
00:47:47,170 --> 00:47:49,239
The more we talk on the phone,

590
00:47:49,400 --> 00:47:51,309
the higher the chance we get
in locating him.

591
00:47:51,710 --> 00:47:53,440
If we get him on the phone often,

592
00:47:54,440 --> 00:47:57,079
we'll be able to get
a rough location of his residence.

593
00:47:57,210 --> 00:47:59,849
We'll ask men in that area
in their 30s and 40s...

594
00:47:59,849 --> 00:48:02,550
and collect their DNA.

595
00:48:03,019 --> 00:48:06,420
Then we'll compare them
to Do Hae Su's DNA.

596
00:48:07,360 --> 00:48:09,320
- Since they're siblings...
- Exactly!

597
00:48:10,230 --> 00:48:12,159
We can identify him!

598
00:48:14,360 --> 00:48:15,530
Why are you so quiet?

599
00:48:15,929 --> 00:48:17,099
I'm sure you're up for this.

600
00:48:19,369 --> 00:48:21,869
You called the police
and gave them a tip?

601
00:48:22,099 --> 00:48:23,239
Yes.

602
00:48:26,710 --> 00:48:27,980
And you told them
you were Do Hyun Su?

603
00:48:32,510 --> 00:48:34,219
That's how they'll move quickly.

604
00:48:35,320 --> 00:48:36,420
We don't have time.

605
00:48:36,889 --> 00:48:39,789
Have you lost your mind?

606
00:48:40,289 --> 00:48:42,119
If my tip turns out to be true,

607
00:48:42,960 --> 00:48:44,590
they promised to protect me.

608
00:48:44,829 --> 00:48:45,989
How can you trust that?

609
00:48:47,030 --> 00:48:48,730
How can you trust the police?

610
00:48:49,329 --> 00:48:52,170
They'll just suck you dry
and backstab you.

611
00:48:53,070 --> 00:48:54,170
Are you stupid?

612
00:48:54,670 --> 00:48:56,000
All you need to do is...

613
00:48:56,000 --> 00:48:58,269
make Yeom Sang Chul
tell you about the accomplice.

614
00:48:59,170 --> 00:49:01,340
Once the police get involved,

615
00:49:01,340 --> 00:49:03,380
he'll find out you betrayed him.

616
00:49:03,809 --> 00:49:04,980
Do you think he'll let you live?

617
00:49:14,659 --> 00:49:16,019
You know, those people
who are confined.

618
00:49:18,360 --> 00:49:20,829
I thought about what Ji Won
would've done...

619
00:49:22,199 --> 00:49:23,329
if she were me.

620
00:49:25,269 --> 00:49:26,539
If it was Ji Won,

621
00:49:27,670 --> 00:49:30,510
she would never have left
those people like that.

622
00:49:34,510 --> 00:49:37,409
Mu Jin, I need your help.

623
00:49:40,179 --> 00:49:43,519
Things might not turn out
as planned.

624
00:49:45,250 --> 00:49:46,960
We need to consider
something unexpected happening too.

625
00:49:47,389 --> 00:49:49,829
What about me? I want to help too.

626
00:49:50,059 --> 00:49:51,260
What can I do?

627
00:49:53,099 --> 00:49:54,159
Nothing.

628
00:49:54,829 --> 00:49:56,130
I want to do something too.

629
00:49:56,429 --> 00:49:58,900
I don't trust you enough
to entrust you...

630
00:49:59,269 --> 00:50:00,500
with something important.

631
00:50:01,170 --> 00:50:02,199
What?

632
00:50:03,210 --> 00:50:04,409
You're unstable.

633
00:50:05,469 --> 00:50:08,110
You almost made a mistake
in front of Ji Won last time.

634
00:50:09,949 --> 00:50:13,480
You might get too emotional
and ruin everything.

635
00:50:14,219 --> 00:50:16,550
Hey, how could you be so rude?

636
00:50:17,150 --> 00:50:18,349
It's okay, Mu Jin.

637
00:50:18,349 --> 00:50:20,289
I know how much
you think of Hyun Su.

638
00:50:21,119 --> 00:50:22,519
This punk doesn't even know that.

639
00:50:23,630 --> 00:50:25,130
What Hyun Su said isn't wrong.

640
00:50:38,869 --> 00:50:39,980
It's Ji Won's number.

641
00:50:41,010 --> 00:50:42,110
Don't answer it.

642
00:50:58,730 --> 00:50:59,900
Yes?

643
00:51:02,130 --> 00:51:04,070
This is Detective Cha Ji Won
of Gangsu Police Station.

644
00:51:05,030 --> 00:51:06,840
I'll put you on speakerphone now.

645
00:51:07,869 --> 00:51:09,400
I'm Captain Lee Woo Chul.

646
00:51:11,110 --> 00:51:13,239
We will believe the tip you gave us.

647
00:51:16,239 --> 00:51:19,610
Let me explain one more time.
There are two steps to the deal.

648
00:51:21,079 --> 00:51:22,679
At the first rendezvous point,

649
00:51:22,679 --> 00:51:24,449
I will hand over the money
to Yeom Sang Chul.

650
00:51:25,650 --> 00:51:27,159
After he checks the money,

651
00:51:27,659 --> 00:51:29,960
he will give me the information
on the second rendezvous point.

652
00:51:31,730 --> 00:51:34,559
I will go to the second
rendezvous point,

653
00:51:35,159 --> 00:51:37,130
and the victims will be handed over
to me.

654
00:51:38,630 --> 00:51:40,469
If there's a problem
during the first meeting,

655
00:51:41,340 --> 00:51:43,909
the second meeting itself
will be canceled, and your chance...

656
00:51:45,239 --> 00:51:48,039
to raid a human trafficking scene
will go down the drain.

657
00:51:49,510 --> 00:51:52,949
So after you meet Mr. Yeom
at first...

658
00:51:53,150 --> 00:51:55,650
and inform us of the
second rendezvous point,

659
00:51:55,880 --> 00:51:59,250
we'll raid the scene when
the victims are handed over, right?

660
00:51:59,690 --> 00:52:01,389
I will be responsible
for the first meeting...

661
00:52:01,719 --> 00:52:05,059
and the police must make no mistake
at the second meeting.

662
00:52:05,329 --> 00:52:09,130
That's how you'll be able to catch
Yeom Sang Chul's whole gang.

663
00:52:09,500 --> 00:52:10,630
Mr. Do.

664
00:52:11,869 --> 00:52:15,400
No matter how much I think about it,
doing this on your own is too risky.

665
00:52:15,840 --> 00:52:17,309
You need police protection.

666
00:52:19,139 --> 00:52:21,610
Where is the first rendezvous point?

667
00:52:22,179 --> 00:52:24,909
No. I won't get involved
with the police...

668
00:52:25,380 --> 00:52:27,019
no matter what happens.

669
00:52:27,719 --> 00:52:30,550
Mr. Do. I said...

670
00:52:30,550 --> 00:52:33,119
we're going to protect you.

671
00:52:33,460 --> 00:52:35,760
Trust us, we won't arrest you.

672
00:52:40,900 --> 00:52:42,059
Mr. Do.

673
00:52:44,170 --> 00:52:45,469
Trust us.

674
00:52:49,800 --> 00:52:54,179
What's important is to keep
Do Hyun Su on the phone...

675
00:52:54,179 --> 00:52:56,679
in order for us to find out
his location.

676
00:52:58,179 --> 00:53:01,179
Ji Won is perfect for that job.

677
00:53:03,989 --> 00:53:05,320
I can't do that.

678
00:53:08,860 --> 00:53:11,730
Do Hyun Su gave us a tip
to save abducted victims...

679
00:53:12,230 --> 00:53:14,260
despite putting himself at risk.

680
00:53:15,929 --> 00:53:19,630
But if we have to backstab
an informant like that...

681
00:53:20,500 --> 00:53:21,969
If that's our job,

682
00:53:24,440 --> 00:53:26,340
I'll leave this investigation team.

683
00:53:28,710 --> 00:53:32,480
We're not some lowly thugs
who backstab informants...

684
00:53:32,480 --> 00:53:34,449
who provide important tips.

685
00:53:34,679 --> 00:53:36,480
You can trust us.

686
00:53:38,849 --> 00:53:41,690
Your safety is not guaranteed
in this operation.

687
00:53:41,690 --> 00:53:43,559
That's what we're concerned about.

688
00:53:45,059 --> 00:53:46,559
We'll do our best...

689
00:53:47,460 --> 00:53:49,800
to protect your identity.

690
00:53:51,500 --> 00:53:53,400
So please put your safety first.

691
00:53:54,400 --> 00:53:57,840
I won't get involved with
the police in any way whatsoever.

692
00:53:58,969 --> 00:54:02,210
You can save the abducted people.

693
00:54:03,309 --> 00:54:05,280
I'll take care of
my part of the deal.

694
00:54:24,969 --> 00:54:26,300
How are the goods?

695
00:54:26,900 --> 00:54:28,769
One of them has an eye problem.

696
00:54:29,269 --> 00:54:30,739
It's diabetes.

697
00:54:32,210 --> 00:54:33,309
What about the kid?

698
00:54:33,840 --> 00:54:35,780
He's a bit dehydrated,
but he'll be okay.

699
00:54:37,409 --> 00:54:39,679
- Just make sure the kid is okay.
- Yes, sir.

700
00:54:40,320 --> 00:54:42,019
Are you sure
Hwang Jung Soon is dead?

701
00:54:42,280 --> 00:54:43,389
Yes, I checked.

702
00:54:44,619 --> 00:54:45,989
It turned out for the better.

703
00:54:46,320 --> 00:54:47,960
We don't have to deal with her now.

704
00:54:51,389 --> 00:54:53,659
She fell into the trap
set by the police.

705
00:54:54,599 --> 00:54:56,500
Man, she was so stupid.

706
00:54:57,869 --> 00:55:01,369
She was getting a bit cocky,
and was starting to annoy me.

707
00:55:04,210 --> 00:55:05,369
Why are you laughing?

708
00:55:06,880 --> 00:55:08,280
She was still one of ours.

709
00:55:09,639 --> 00:55:10,780
I'm sorry, sir.

710
00:55:10,980 --> 00:55:13,250
We better lay low for a while
after this deal.

711
00:55:15,420 --> 00:55:17,289
Load the rest of the goods
on the boat now.

712
00:55:17,889 --> 00:55:18,889
Yes, sir.

713
00:55:22,159 --> 00:55:23,260
I'm back, sir.

714
00:55:35,699 --> 00:55:37,670
It's nice to see him again
after so long.

715
00:55:39,070 --> 00:55:41,210
He used to hang out
with Do Min Seok so much.

716
00:55:41,909 --> 00:55:43,610
But he literally vanished lately.

717
00:55:56,090 --> 00:55:57,230
I'm a man who believes...

718
00:55:58,630 --> 00:56:02,599
that money can solve
the easiest problems in life.

719
00:56:03,260 --> 00:56:04,369
But...

720
00:56:05,829 --> 00:56:07,800
I'm worried this won't solve
anything...

721
00:56:07,969 --> 00:56:10,440
but only make matters worse.

722
00:56:11,909 --> 00:56:13,070
I'll solve it.

723
00:56:14,940 --> 00:56:16,039
Hyun Su.

724
00:56:18,809 --> 00:56:20,820
I'll give you ten times this amount.

725
00:56:24,650 --> 00:56:26,420
Just leave without anyone
knowing about it.

726
00:56:28,219 --> 00:56:30,019
Don't worry about your family.

727
00:56:31,489 --> 00:56:33,659
I'll take care of the rest.

728
00:56:40,639 --> 00:56:41,800
No.

729
00:56:43,139 --> 00:56:44,269
Why?

730
00:56:45,269 --> 00:56:49,440
I don't want to entrust you
with my family.

731
00:56:51,050 --> 00:56:53,519
What do you think of me?

732
00:56:56,920 --> 00:56:58,719
You're a similar human being
like me.

733
00:56:59,750 --> 00:57:00,789
What?

734
00:57:01,760 --> 00:57:03,260
A human being...

735
00:57:03,860 --> 00:57:06,530
who does whatever it takes
in order to get what he wants.

736
00:57:12,829 --> 00:57:13,969
What about you?

737
00:57:15,300 --> 00:57:18,170
Will you be able to leave
your family in my trust?

738
00:57:20,110 --> 00:57:21,179
Good.

739
00:57:23,010 --> 00:57:24,809
I feel more relaxed...

740
00:57:25,750 --> 00:57:27,480
hearing your honest remarks.

741
00:57:30,449 --> 00:57:33,960
Thank goodness people like us...

742
00:57:34,889 --> 00:57:36,320
have the same goal.

743
00:57:41,929 --> 00:57:43,670
I'll get going.

744
00:57:44,469 --> 00:57:45,469
Okay.

745
00:57:50,369 --> 00:57:51,409
Hyun Su.

746
00:57:59,150 --> 00:58:00,179
Take care.

747
00:58:19,070 --> 00:58:20,900
I said, who reported it?

748
00:58:20,969 --> 00:58:22,000
I can't tell you.

749
00:58:24,610 --> 00:58:26,340
You won't tell me the identity
of the informant,

750
00:58:26,840 --> 00:58:28,039
yet you want backup?

751
00:58:28,510 --> 00:58:29,510
Yes.

752
00:58:29,639 --> 00:58:31,250
Please give us as many men
you can afford.

753
00:58:32,949 --> 00:58:36,550
In order to solve the Yeonju
Serial Murder Case flawlessly,

754
00:58:37,619 --> 00:58:39,019
we must catch Yeom Sang Chul.

755
00:58:40,619 --> 00:58:42,590
Woo Chul.
Look straight into my eyes.

756
00:58:48,960 --> 00:58:50,059
You're sure of this, right?

757
00:59:04,949 --> 00:59:05,949
Ji Won.

758
00:59:06,480 --> 00:59:08,980
I'll only say this once,
so listen to me carefully.

759
00:59:11,489 --> 00:59:13,989
I think we're lucky to have you
on our team.

760
00:59:14,860 --> 00:59:17,789
I felt it again today.

761
00:59:22,630 --> 00:59:23,969
What's this?

762
00:59:25,929 --> 00:59:27,670
Are you a little moved?

763
00:59:29,440 --> 00:59:30,809
You're so slow.

764
00:59:31,039 --> 00:59:34,480
It's not that. She's feeling sick...

765
00:59:35,079 --> 00:59:36,139
from your corny lines.

766
00:59:36,679 --> 00:59:38,710
It's okay, you can throw up.

767
00:59:39,050 --> 00:59:41,349
You, come here. Come over here.

768
00:59:42,349 --> 00:59:44,019
I'll talk to you after this call.

769
00:59:46,960 --> 00:59:47,960
Yes.

770
00:59:48,059 --> 00:59:51,559
I finished restoring
the formatted recorder.

771
01:00:19,849 --> 01:00:20,860
(Accept, Decline)

772
01:00:35,070 --> 01:00:37,309
- Yes?
- I'm curious about something.

773
01:00:38,639 --> 01:00:41,909
I received your bag
from Nam Soon Gil's wife.

774
01:00:44,949 --> 01:00:47,420
I listened to the recorder
from the bag.

775
01:00:50,690 --> 01:00:52,219
Can you tell me...

776
01:00:54,190 --> 01:00:55,559
whose voice it was?

777
01:01:01,599 --> 01:01:03,800
- If you don't want to tell me...
- It's my mom.

778
01:01:06,369 --> 01:01:07,440
What?

779
01:01:08,800 --> 01:01:09,969
1997.

780
01:01:11,909 --> 01:01:14,010
It was just before Mom went missing.

781
01:01:16,579 --> 01:01:20,210
I was given that recorder
to cherish Mom's voice.

782
01:01:22,150 --> 01:01:24,650
Father reported Mom missing,

783
01:01:25,920 --> 01:01:28,489
and the police took away her stuff.

784
01:01:29,559 --> 01:01:30,690
I thought...

785
01:01:31,989 --> 01:01:34,159
they'd take everything from me
if I said anything.

786
01:01:38,030 --> 01:01:39,070
You must have...

787
01:01:41,340 --> 01:01:42,969
really loved your mother.

788
01:01:44,809 --> 01:01:46,269
A psychiatrist...

789
01:01:46,570 --> 01:01:50,210
told me I lack emotional empathy.

790
01:01:52,349 --> 01:01:54,880
It's impossible for me
to have such feelings.

791
01:01:57,820 --> 01:02:00,519
Then why did you cherish it
for such a long time?

792
01:02:03,789 --> 01:02:05,130
I'm not sure about that.

793
01:02:07,099 --> 01:02:09,800
I was never diagnosed about
the motive for such behavior.

794
01:02:11,329 --> 01:02:13,130
I won't be able
to explain that for you.

795
01:02:17,170 --> 01:02:18,269
It's because...

796
01:02:25,849 --> 01:02:27,679
I don't want to lie to you.

797
01:02:31,349 --> 01:02:32,389
Mr. Do Hyun Su.

798
01:02:35,789 --> 01:02:36,860
Yes?

799
01:02:40,460 --> 01:02:41,500
Please...

800
01:02:46,469 --> 01:02:47,699
don't get hurt.

801
01:02:51,739 --> 01:02:52,739
What?

802
01:02:53,670 --> 01:02:55,139
I'm hanging up.

803
01:03:10,090 --> 01:03:11,389
I'll call you...

804
01:03:12,460 --> 01:03:14,260
around 10pm later.

805
01:03:43,590 --> 01:03:44,960
In my opinion,

806
01:03:45,760 --> 01:03:47,530
the sound recorded
on the cassette tape...

807
01:03:47,800 --> 01:03:50,530
incites Hyun Su's aggression
and violent behavior,

808
01:03:50,769 --> 01:03:52,099
and even triggers it.

809
01:03:59,139 --> 01:04:00,239
Detective Cha?

810
01:04:01,210 --> 01:04:02,610
Why didn't you know?

811
01:04:03,110 --> 01:04:04,110
What?

812
01:04:04,210 --> 01:04:07,619
Why didn't you think that recording
could be something...

813
01:04:07,619 --> 01:04:08,920
his mother left behind?

814
01:04:09,380 --> 01:04:11,719
What are you talking about,
Detective Cha?

815
01:04:12,019 --> 01:04:14,760
At the time you consulted him,
his mother just went missing.

816
01:04:15,260 --> 01:04:18,760
It's obvious what a young child
would get obsessed over.

817
01:04:18,989 --> 01:04:20,900
It's natural for any ordinary kid.

818
01:04:21,199 --> 01:04:23,659
- Detective Cha.
- You should've known.

819
01:04:24,630 --> 01:04:27,369
You were the only person
who could've helped him then.

820
01:04:27,869 --> 01:04:29,969
